-- Slovene Banks Liabilities Quality Worsens: Govt Institute
-- B y   B o r i s   C e r n i
-- 2013-10-07T09:45:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-10-07/slovene-banks-liabilities-quality-worsens-govt-institute.html
Size of loans to Slovenian cos. was
lowest this year in August, govt forecasting institute says in
e-mailed statement.
* Loans to cos. down by EU1.2b in 8 months through August:
institute
* Household deposits at banks lower, institute says, without
providing figures
* Bad loans rise “significantly” by EU260m in July, represent
16.9% of all liabilities: institute
* NOTE:  Central bank  said Oct. 1 bad loans rose to EU7.9b; link
to story: NSN MTZD3B6JTSFH <GO>
* NOTE: Slovenia’s economy will shrink more than previously
forecast next year as ailing banking industry and austerity
measures prevent recovery, govt’s economic institute said Oct.
